ExecDesc.value: Apple QuickTime Plugin SetLanguage Buffer Overflow(IPv6)

EngDesc.value: A stack buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Apple QuickTime. The vulnerability is due to insufficient bounds checking when parsing parameters to the IQTPluginControl::SetLanguage COM method inside the QuickTime plugin. This vulnerability can be exploited by a remote attacker by enticing the target user to open a specially crafted HTML page containing an embedded video with the affected application. Successful exploitation could result in arbitrary code injection and execution in the context of the currently logged-in user.
